.StringBuilder` and its constructor. It seems unsupported, but maybe the syntax for Graal Native reflect config could accept older formats for JDK classes. I also wonder if `ChildSerializable` has a public constructor; it does, which is good. If the enclosing test class lacks reflection config, that means inner static classes are present. \\n\\nI’m noticing coverage concerns on specific lines, but as long as the reflection config is in place, I think we should be fine. I’m also pondering whether I can call `convertEscaped` via `load`, since direct protected calls from tests might be tricky.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage improvements for `liquibase.serializer.AbstractLiquibaseSerializable`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/5.0.1/src/test/java/org_liquibase/liquibase_core/AbstractLiquibaseSerializableTest.java`\n- Covered reflective constructor paths in `load(...)` for:\n  - collection field wrapper nodes\n  - direct collection element nodes\n  - nested `LiquibaseSerializable` fields\n- Covered `convertEscaped(...)` paths for:\n  - `Class.forName(...)`\n  - `getConstructor(long.class).newInstance(...)`\n  - `getConstructor(String.class).newInstance(...)`\n- Updated test native-image reflection config:\n  - `tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/5.0.1/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/test/reflect-config.json`\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_013fbec7b215339c0169f6dc748490819d9bff846e02423fb9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1611, "output": 715, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27414, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777785962309, "responseId": "resp_013fbec7b215339c0169f6dc6ac21c819d8d73df07d1b15f8b"}, "toolResults": []}
